text: Yana Urqu (Quechua yana black, urqu mountain, "black mountain", Hispanicized spelling Yanaorjo) is a mountain in the eastern extensions of the Willkapampa mountain range in the Andes of Peru. It is located in the Cusco Region, Urubamba Province, Ollantaytambo District, southwest of Ollantaytambo.escale.minedu.gob.pe - UGEL map of the Urubamba Province (Cusco Region) ==References== Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Cusco Region
